The mayor at the end of the conference remitted the three-coloured band: "I am a man of the institutions and as all men I will wait with serenity the commission for access and give him all the support, all the assistance and all the documentation that will serve. Because Bari is a city that has fourteen Mafia clans, it is true - it has remembered the first citizen -. But above all it is a city that resists organized crime. A city that doesn't bend to the head. A city that doesn't turn on the other side. A city that holds its head high with dignity. And we always remember that. We have to be proud of the bears for good. That are many more than people who are not for good and criminals."
