"Today this is an act of self-defense not of the mayor, not of the city council, an act of self-defense of our city. I've been corrected since I became mayor of this city. I wore the band, put my party card in the drawer and I was the mayor of all. Especially those who didn't vote for me and the same thing I did as representative of the National Association of Municipalities. I was the president of all. Especially those who didn't have my political origin. And I did so with honor, with discipline, the mayor and the president of the ANCI, I have always guaranteed institutional respect to the governments that have succeeded in these years and I have seen so many in ten years. And I think everyone can recognize me." This was said by the mayor of Bari, Antonio Decaro, during a long press conference convened in the council hall of Palazzo di Città in the aftermath of the measure of inspection access arranged by the Minister of the Interior to the Municipality of Bari.
