&nbsp;
"I went to the Interior Minister - he told -. And I told him 'Ministro I represent the institutions. I'm mayor. I also represent the other mayors. And restless to see that there is a group of MPs from the center of my Region who went to his room, they took a photograph, went out, made a press conference saying that they asked the minister, following the arrests that had been in the city of Bari, an inspection of the municipality because with that inspection they had to dissolve the municipality of Bari by mafia. I have not reacted because I represent the institutions. Among those MPs there are D'Attis (Mauro D'Attis, regional commissioner of Forza Italia, ndr), who today is vice-president of the anti-mafia commission, and the other instead is the vice-minister of justice Sisto (Francesco Paolo Sisto, ndr), who together with another vice-minister to health (Marcello Gemmato, ndr) have gone from the members of the government to the local interior, to try to try to try to try to try to try to try to try to try to try to try to try
<h2>Decaro, persons arrested were on the other side political
Among the people arrested during the operation "Codice Interno", coordinated by the District Direction Antimafia of Bari, which led to the execution of 137 custodians, there were the former regional councilman Giacomo Olivieri and his wife Maria Carmen Lorusso (at the domiciles), elected municipal councilman in Bari with the list "Di Rella Mayor", then passed in majority with "Sud al Centro". "Those people were not candidates with my political side, but on the other hand," said Mayor Antonio Decaro during a press conference at Palazzo di Citta', following the provision of inspection access provided by the Minister of Interior at the Municipality of Bari. The first citizen showed newspaper articles, photos, with which the whole room was covered: "The flirtation of Forza Italia with Olivieri and Canonico, were Mauro D'Attis and Francesco Paolo Sisto, then heavily attacked by their party, to make an electoral agreement. They made two civic lists: in one - that of Canon - there was Francesca Ferri (stop in 2022, ndr) for mafia exchange vote in the municipality of Valenzano and a few days ago was arrested Lorusso, wife of Olivieri. So I thought that photograph (of the MPs Apulian from the Minister Piantedosi, ndr) served to say 'we anticipate, we attack the mayor, so 'we put our hands on not to fall is said in Bari'. But no, there was probably a drawing."
