The coin of Adriano, which will be beaten in June, had been exposed for many years to the British Museum of London and was commissioned by the emperor after the completion of the Vallo to him titled, in 130 AD. In June will auction a trio of &nbsp; coinage &nbsp; british reconfigurants including the 'Petition Crown' of 1633 Charles II, whose value is highly estimated in 750 thousand The other coin is the Testoon of Henry VIII of 1544 and that of King Charles I depicted in Oxford during the Civil War, built in 1644. "These &nbsp;monete&nbsp; they are not only spectacular for the artistic realization of important moments in the history of ancient Rome and the British monarchy - underlined the director of Numismatica Ars Classica, Arturo Russo - but also for their 'pedigree'. We are excited to offer collectors the opportunity to buy a piece of History." &nbsp;
