AGI - In Italy 57% of people are altogether happy and hopeful, but at the same time they say very worried and tired. The state of good health and satisfying personal relationships are the main reasons for happiness, while the national economic situation is mainly the cause of dissatisfaction. It reveals an Ipsos investigation of the Public Affairs team, conducted on the occasion of the International Day of Happiness 2024, established by the UN 12 years ago.
&nbsp;
The World Happiness Report 2024, released just for this occasion, assigns Italy the 41st place in the global ranking of happiness, very behind compared to several of its European neighbors.&nbsp; Half of the respondents rated their level of happiness as at least enough while 16% consider themselves seriously unhappy. Authentic happiness is pretty low in the ranking, proven by only 4% of people.
&nbsp;
At the generational level, the youth of the GenZ are happier, who declare themselves more determined and carefree than the average of the Italians, and the Boomers, on average more hopeful. The members of Generation X and Millennials are far less happy: anger and apathy characterize the first, fatigue, frustration and melancholy seconds.
<br For Italians health is in the first place and bad psycho-physical conditions are considered by 65% as the main threat to happiness, decidedly more than a situation of economic poverty. In the aspirations of the Italians the fundamental triad for happiness is constituted by good health (indicated by 44%), to be well with your family (38%) and not to have economic concerns (35%). A satisfactory relational sphere is very important to contribute to the happiness of the Italians - that is, relations with friends, relatives and people living in the entourage, including colleagues - and on this front, more than two thirds of the respondents were satisfied. They also take into account the quality of free time (62%) and the sentimental sphere (60%).
&nbsp;
<div </div
<br As regards the economic situation, the satisfaction values decrease: 54% are satisfied with the economic conditions of their family, 48% for the situation in their own city or region and only 28% for the national economic situation.
<br A moderate serenity, therefore, which is not distributed homogeneously in society. The concern is the emotion mainly felt, followed by tiredness and hope. Italian men are on average happier, especially more hopeful, optimistic and serene, while women tend to be more concerned, tired and confused.

